title: Cache Read-Through with Stampede Prevention

participant Client A as A
participant Client B as B
participant App Server as App
participant Redis as Cache
participant PostgreSQL as DB

A->>App: GET /products/99
App->>Cache: GET product:99
Cache-->>App: (nil)
note right of App: Cache miss
App->>Cache: SET product:99:lock NX EX 5
Cache-->>App: OK (lock acquired)
note over App: This request populates cache
B->>App: GET /products/99
App->>Cache: GET product:99
Cache-->>App: (nil)
App->>Cache: SET product:99:lock NX EX 5
Cache-->>App: (nil) - lock exists
note right of App: Wait with backoff
App->>DB: SELECT * FROM products WHERE id=99
DB-->>App: { id:99, name:Widget, price:29.99 }
App->>Cache: SETEX product:99 600 { ... }
Cache-->>App: OK
App->>Cache: DEL product:99:lock
Cache-->>App: OK
App-->>A: 200 { id:99, name:Widget }
note over App: Client B retries
App->>Cache: GET product:99
Cache-->>App: { id:99, name:Widget }
note right of App: Cache hit!
App-->>B: 200 { id:99, name:Widget }
